Next up [Sarah](https://twitter.com/everydayfoxlife) and
[Roy](https://twitter.com/kotowari) presented various games made at game jams
this year. You can check out all their games at
[itch.io](https://everydayfoxlife.itch.io/) - here's a link to the latest:

!img dreameater.jpg

!embed https://everydayfoxlife.itch.io/dream-eater
<iframe width="744" frameborder="0"  src="https://itch.io/embed/166927"></iframe>

[Takaaki Ichijo](https://twitter.com/ttwcodeout) talked about the difficulty of
indie game development and gave advice about finishing in spite of it. He also
showed off his game [Back in 1995](http://backin1995.com/), a retro mystery
adventure game for PC.

!embed https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=T5Kw8YvKCdE
<iframe width="612" height="344" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/T5Kw8YvKCdE?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" gesture="media" allow="encrypted-media" allowfullscreen></iframe>

Finally [Rekcahdam](https://twitter.com/Rekcahdam) showed off
[Band Saga](http://www.bandsaga.com/), his musical roguelike.

!embed https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Zs-Y0dYBwDM
<iframe width="612" height="344" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/Zs-Y0dYBwDM?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" gesture="media" allow="encrypted-media" allowfullscreen></iframe>

That was it for this year's Tokyo Indies - catch you next time! ğŸ®
